sec.p:
By 2 January 2021, we had observed the recurrent outbreaks of COVID-19 in many countries. Thus, the previous single wave logistic model can no longer appropriately depict the whole picture of the current dynamics of the epidemic outbreak. For this reason, we have developed a revised version of the previous possible solutions to this dilemma. A logistic function has been used in previous studies to depict the cumulative daily number of COVID-19 cases in the early phase of the epidemic outbreak [36]. Here, we used the logistic model of multiple waves sigmoid model to solve this problem. We reasoned that the entire time series data could be divided into multiple waves, which is denoted with a sigmoid function. Using the multiple waves sigmoid model, the cumulative number of the infected cases in any given region I(t) can be calculated by:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
